  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Integrated Assistance Focusing on WASH for IDPs in camps in North Kivu</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project provides water, sanitation and hygiene (WASH) services to people living in IDP camps in Birambizo, Mweso, Goma and Karisimbi. The intervention ensures long-term and equitable access to WASH services, building capacity of camp committees to manage and maintain the provision of services in the camps. Mercy Corps will provide lasting solutions for providing water to the camps, including gravity-fed water systems, pumps and water treatment systems, and will monitor quality to make sure it meets minimum standards. In addition to water, Mercy Corps is providing latrines, hand-washing stations, and washing stations, and put in place systems for garbage disposal. Committees will be trained to manage and maintain all services and infrastructure, and the entire population benefits from training and outreach campaigns in hygiene-related behavior change.</narrative>
  </description>
